About
Privacy
We use web analytics tools to understand how visitors interact with our site and improve our services. Specifically, we use:
Cloudflare Web Analytics:
This tool is a lightweight, privacy-first web analytics service that does not use cookies or localStorage to collect usage metrics. It does not track users across sites or collect personal information. For more details, please refer to
Cloudflare's Privacy Policy
and
GDPR Compliance page
.
Google Tag Manager:
This tool helps us manage and deploy marketing on our website. It allows us to measure advertising ROI. For more information about how Google Tag Manager handles data, please refer to
Google's Privacy Policy
.
Data Collection and Use
Personal Data:
We do not collect, transmit, distribute, or sell your personal data without your explicit consent.
Non-Personal Data:
We may collect non-personal data, such as anonymized usage statistics, for improving our services.
Newsletter
If you subscribe to our newsletter, we will collect your email address to send you updates about our company, new releases, and other relevant information. You can unsubscribe at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in any newsletter email.
Data Security
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk of personal data breaches. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and we cannot guarantee absolute security. Therefore, we do not warrant or guarantee the security of any information you transmit to us, and you do so at your own risk.
Your Rights (EU Residents)
Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have the right to access, correct, delete, restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data, and to request data portability. You may also withdraw your consent at any time. To exercise these rights, please contact us.
Children's Privacy
Our services are not directed to individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal data from a child, we will delete such data from our records.
Cookies
We do not use cookies for tracking purposes. However, please be aware that third-party services may use cookies or similar technologies. For more information on how they handle cookies and data, please refer to their respective privacy policies.
Links to External Websites
This website includes hypertext links to external websites. Since we do not have control over these third-party websites, we cannot assume responsibility for their content or actions.
Legal
We may disclose your personal data in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to:
Comply with a legal obligation.
Protect and defend our rights or property.
Prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with our services.
Protect the personal safety of users of our services or the public.
Protect against legal liability.
